The paper deals with blind deconvolution, which is a problem commonly encountered in signal processing and communication systems. The paper uses mathematical techniques to analyze the ambiguity space of blind deconvolution, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with signal processing and image processing, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also uses sparse models for regularizing blind deconvolution, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the paper could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), as it deals with image processing and communication systems.
